# {{ bakery.project_name }} — frontend (Next.js 16 App Router)

> Generated by [`django-bakery`](https://github.com/Axionore/Django-Barkery). Next.js 16 · React 19 · TypeScript 6 · Radix Themes 4 · App Router · session-cookie auth via allauth headless.

The frontend talks to Django via **session cookies** — no JWT in localStorage, no token in JS. Django's `sessionid` cookie (HttpOnly, SameSite=Lax) is the only credential.

## Quickstart

```bash
pnpm install
pnpm --filter frontend dev      # next on http://localhost:{{ bakery.frontend_dev_port }}

# OR with the full stack:
docker compose -f compose.local.yml up
```

Next.js `rewrites` send `/api`, `/_allauth`, `/static`, `/media` to Django on `:8000`. Browser sees them as same-origin → cookies + CSRF Just Work.

## Server vs Client Components

Next.js 16 with the App Router mixes two execution models. We pick the right one per page:

| Page | Why this kind |
| --- | --- |
| `app/page.tsx` (Home) | **Server** — reads `currentUser()` server-side; no client-side waterfall |
| `app/about/page.tsx` | **Server** — static; no client interaction |
| `app/account/login` | **Client** (`"use client"`) — handles form state |
| `app/account/signup` | **Client** — form state |
| `app/account/profile` | **Server** + `redirect()` — auth gate runs on server; user never sees a flash |
| `app/account/mfa-challenge` | **Client** — form |
| `app/account/mfa-activate` | **Client** — useEffect-driven enrollment |
| `app/account/recovery-codes` | **Client** — useEffect-driven fetch |

`app/layout.tsx` is a Server Component that reads the session via `currentUser()` (which uses `next/headers`'s `cookies()`) and seeds the initial state into `<Providers initialUser={user}>`. The Client Components hydrate into the same store via Zustand.

