## Authentication contract

```
POST /_allauth/browser/v1/auth/login         (Client via fetch with credentials)
  200 → user is signed in ({ data.user })
  401 + flows[].id === "mfa_authenticate" → MFA challenge screen
  401 + flows[].id === "verify_email"     → "check your email" screen
  401 (no flows) → invalid credentials
  429 → cool-down
```

Server-side, the same allauth session endpoint is called via `fetch` with the user's cookie forwarded — see `lib/auth/server.ts::fetchSessionServer`. The `"server-only"` import in that file ensures the browser bundle can never accidentally include it.

### Why session cookies and not JWTs?

`localStorage` is an OWASP A02 anti-pattern — XSS becomes total account takeover. With Django session cookies:
- `sessionid` is `HttpOnly` — XSS cannot read it.
- `SameSite=Lax` blocks cross-site cookie forwarding.
- The `csrftoken` cookie is the only cookie JS reads, useful only same-site.

For mobile / IoT consumers of `/api`, use [django-ninja-jwt](https://django-ninja.dev/guides/authentication/#django-ninja-jwt) or [SimpleJWT](https://django-rest-framework-simplejwt.readthedocs.io/) at a separate `/api/token/*` namespace.

## Security baseline (already on)

- `next.config.ts` ships `X-Frame-Options: DENY`, `Referrer-Policy: same-origin`, `X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff`, and a strict `Permissions-Policy` (camera, microphone, geolocation, payment all denied).
- `productionBrowserSourceMaps: false` — no source maps in prod (OWASP A09).
- Same-origin rewrites — no wildcard CORS (OWASP A05).
- `react/no-danger` ESLint rule — banned raw-HTML API (OWASP A03).
- `lib/auth/server.ts` is marked `"server-only"` — bundle-time guard against leaking the cookie-aware code into the browser.
- Sentry SDK (when `use_sentry=true`) auto-installed via `@sentry/nextjs`; strips `Cookie` / `Authorization` / `X-CSRFToken` in `beforeSend`.

